02/05/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Bosnian Serb government has found six mass graves in Srebrenica, an official announced Friday (30 April). 
Milan Bogdanic, who heads a government-appointed commission to investigate the 1995 massacre, said members of his panel had visited the sites but found it difficult to estimate how many people are buried there. 
The commission has until June to file a report on Srebrenica. 
It has complained repeatedly of obstruction by Bosnian Serb authorities. 
A report to the government Friday suggested, however, that significant progress has been made in the last two weeks.
In other news, Turkish State Minister Kursad Tuzmen met with BiH cabinet officials in Sarajevo on Friday. 
They discussed economic, political and regional co-operation and ways to boost bilateral relations. 
(Anadolu Agency, PBS BiH - 01/05/04; AP, AFP, Fena - 30/04/04)
